Full Description: Medical Software Associates was originally known as Clinical Data Systems. Their business specializes in the support of computer systems and information technology for small and medium sized medical practices. Have a look at us! Clinical Data Systems was founded in 1991 by Gary Higbee as a spin-off of his regional forms company, the Association Connection. This company supplied specialized forms with a focus on the medical industry. Gary saw an opportunity to combine his over 25 years of computer knowledge with a good practice management software system. At that time the company became an authorized dealer for Medical Manager. In 2003 they began operating the company under Medical Software Associates, serving customers in several states. They became authorized to represent the MicroMD product which provides practice management and electronic records. Currently they also represent and support EDI ClaimManager, Aprima, DRS, MDsuite, dashboardMD, Dragon Medical, and other products. They  exist to provide and support the best products in their service areas for medical practices. The product scope includes practice management, electronic medical records, document imaging software, automated appointment confirmations solutions, electronic data interchange (EDI) services, as well as claims managements systems. In addition to their distinctly medical products they offer complete computer network installation and support, actively monitored backup, antivirus, and other solutions. They provide ongoing customer service, maintenance, support and training for all the products they offer. So from paper forms in the mainframe days to now, when you can follow us on Facebook and Twitter, they keep changing to help their customers solve problems.

Description: Care Technology Systems provides data analytics and remote monitoring services to improve the safety of seniors.
Full Description: Care Technology Systems provides data analytics and remote monitoring services to improve the safety of seniors. Care Technology Systems announced the availability of CTS' monitoring suite on the 2net(TM) Platform operated by Qualcomm Life Inc. As organizations across the country are beginning to embrace the positive benefits of remote monitoring, many have been frustrated that they have to cobble together disparate solutions from different vendors. By bringing together PERS, ADL, and Biometric Monitoring all on one 2net Platform, Care Technology Systems is offering an unrivaled value proposition that is a win for plans, providers, and patients.  Based in Nashville, Tennessee, Care Technology Systems has united a range of leading-edge technologies and communications media to help seniors maintain their independence and lifestyle as they age in place. The key to the system is that it has no interface to frustrate the user. Its wireless technology works silently in the background to keep both families and staff informed 24/7 of the senior's lifestyle movements and requires nothing of the senior or patient to perform its role. If there are issues or threats, caregivers close by and far away are immediately notified through various communications channels -- including social media -- and can respond appropriately. A cloud-based system, Qualcomm Life's 2net Platform enables companies, providers, and users to capture data from any wireless medical device and deliver it to integrated portals or databases, storing it in a secure and reliable system. Information can be easily retrieved by physicians, caregivers, or other critical audiences, such as designated healthcare service companies, providers, payors, pharmaceutical companies, and application/device collaborators, for use in healthcare decisions. CTS utilizes the 2net Platform to provide PERS, ADL monitoring, and biometrics.
Industry Groups: Health Care, Internet Services, Sales and Marketing

Description: Dairyland Shrimp, LLC is a family owned business located in Westby, Wisconsin.
Full Description: Dairyland Shrimp, LLC is a family owned business located in Westby, Wisconsin. Known for being America‚Äôs Dairyland, they felt a name like Dairyland Shrimp was a bit unique since they probably have more cows than the Gulf has shrimp. Not really, but they like to humor ourselves. Their farm is located in the heart of the Kickapoo Valley where the organically grown food industry is booming, so the concept of farming locally raised Pacific White shrimp year-round through an environmentally friendly ‚Äúbio floc‚Äù process sparked their interest. Upon hearing about bio-floc shrimp farming they immediately recognized the value of offering fresh, locally grown shrimp and set out to learn more. They then found Northern Tide Shrimp Farm and decided to take a road trip to Minnesota to learn more about the biofloc process. After taking a tour they bought a couple of pounds of shrimp and were blown away by the flavor and freshness and the decision was made to embark on the endeavor of ethically farming Pacific White Shrimp, Litopenaeus vannamei, within an indoor zero waste re-circulating bio-floc system. their children love shrimp. knowing what they now know about imported shrimp their family no longer eats them. At Dairyland they offer more than just shrimp, they offer a healthy, hormone, and pathogen free family farm raised product that consumers can feel good about eating.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Biotechnology, Food and Beverage, Science and Engineering
